SSH Tunnel to re-route internet traffic
=======================================
ssh -D 8080 -N -q <username of remote server>@<public IP of remote server> -p <public SSH port of remote server>

For Chrome/Chromium-based Browsers
----------------------------------
Go to Settings > Privacy and security > Security > Manage certificates > Authorities.
Alternatively, you can use an extension like FoxyProxy to manage your proxy settings more easily.
Set up a manual proxy configuration:
Manual proxy configuration:
HTTP proxy: localhost
Port: 8080
HTTPS proxy: localhost
Port: 8080
SOCKS proxy:
SOCKS Version: 5
Host: localhost
Port: 8080

For Firefox
-----------
Go to Settings > Network Settings > Settings... > Settings.
Select Manual proxy configuration.
Set:
SOCKS Host: 127.0.0.1
Port: 8080
SOCKS Version: 5
